Apr 6 2008 	Perfect Place	We spent 2 weeks in the San Francisco area in March which included 5 nights at the Ocean Park Motel. We are English and had this notion of a typical American family-run motel and I'm pleased to say that it was exactly what we'd hoped for. The motel itself is located in a quiet part of SF but the tram stop is located right across the street so getting to and from the city centre is very easy. The ocean itself is a 5-minute walk and the zoo is a couple of minutes away. We just loved the tranquil atmosphere and the way the rooms looked out onto a beautiful quiet courtyard (see photos!). SF is a typical busy city with lots to see and do, and it was great to be able to come back each night to this lovely peaceful place. You also felt that you were left alone by the staff - sounds strange, but they provided everything you needed and were always there if you wanted advice or had a problem but weren't 'in your face' like some of the other places we stayed.There was plenty of car parking space and it was easy to get to and from the motel by road, but we found it much easier to use the tram to explore the city itself.Our room was clean, spacious and had everything we needed - maybe not the luxuries you'd expect from a more expensive hotel, but we definitely didn't want for anything. even things like irons, hair dryers etc. were provided willingly if you asked.Would definitely stay here again if are ever in SF!	
