Apr 2 2008	Charming bit of San Fransico history.	Staying at the Ocean Park was coming back to my California roots. The space was charming and comfy. I love seeing this old gem restored and functional.I felt very comfortable, and had a wonderful sleep the night before a long flight.The owners made sure that all guests were well taken care of. So nice to experience the small town feel in the big city. Being along the coast and close to the airport, can't be beat. Ocean Park is my favorite Bay Area stopover!	
Feb 22 2008 	OK Hotel Nice Location	We stayed at the Ocean Park while visiting our daughter at SFSU. The manager was nice and the hotel is located in a residential area. The rooms are dated but quaint. I guess that's part of the classic art deco feel of the hotel. The Ocean Park is very close to the SF Zoo and Beach. For a good place to eat try the Bashful Bull Restaurant a few blocks walk into the neighborhood (Great Breakfast All Day!). Now for the caveat, if you are a light sleeper beware of the Muni Train which passes right in front of the hotel. Our room was at the front of the hotel and the train made a heck of a racket on a regular basis (I didn't sleep well but my wife did). I can't say how loud the train was for those lucky enough to get a room at the rear of the hotel. Overall, our stay wasn't bad but for $125/night I will probably try another hotel just to compare.	
Feb 16 2008	Retro Motor Motel	This is a cute little motor court motel that is everything motels aren't anymore. The art deco exterior is great and the updated interior are awesome. This is old school and you must have no 'motel' expectations when you check in. This is a charming, friendly, clean and comfy place to stay just a couple of blocks from the beach. Take advantage of the list of ideas for touring, dining, and transportation provided when you check in as well. If we stay in SF again, we will definitely stay here.	
Jan 27 2008 	Nice Place!	This was a great place and a very good choice. It is two blocks from the beach, and across the street from the zoo and the train stop to downdown and all of SF. All of SF's major parks were very nearby and all services within a mile. Great location! The place itself has an immaculate green courtyard and grounds and the unit I stayed in was a one bedroom with a kitchen and very spacious, like a one bedroom apartment. Also the value was excellent, it was the same price as some of the tiny hotel rooms around there but vastly superior in every respect. I'll definately stay there agian when visiting SF. Very nice, friendly owners too. I highly recomment it.	
Jan 17 2008 	Loved Ocean Park Motel	I have stayed in various hotels in San Francisco (all price ranges) and found that Ocean Park Motel was the very best value and we enjoyed the friendly service, great location and easy access, and very convenient (and FREE) onsite parking. I know that the City and accommodations can be very noisy no matter where you are and we found that this location was one of the quietest. I have also had rooms where you could barely move. This was not the case at Ocean Park Motel. Our room and bathroom were spacious (we had an upstairs room with a microwave and queen and twin bed). It was very easy to travel back and forth from our room to visit our daughter who is now living on the SFSU campus. If we wanted, we could have easily walked to the beach or the zoo from the Motel. We plan many more visits and will always stay at Ocean Park Motel, without a doubt.	
Nov 25 2007 	Neighborhood Charm	If you want to stay at a place that is rich in local history where the owners live on the property and the neighbors commute on the streetcar that runs by your door then this is the place for you. A list of favorite neighborhood restaurants and ear plugs are thoughtfully given to you upon check-in along with a map of the city with transit options. Hop a bus to the DeYoung museum then dine on some of the finest crab in SF - all without driving a car on those nerve wracking hills! Helpful local staff provide opportunities for experiences off the beaten tourist path. The rooms are simple and clean. The price/value/experience ratio is great. I stay here whenever I am in SF for an art fair.	
Nov 13 2007 	Quirky and Charming	I like to stay in quirky little places like this. Being the first motel in San Francisco, you can't expect the polish of a franchise hotel, or the super smooth edges of the super expensive places. I like the history. Art Deco/Art Nouveau of this place is really charming. The rooms are a little small and awkward. But the beds were super comfortable! I don't sleep that well on my own bed (mostly because the cat walks on my face). It was very clean inside and out. Please do not include the sidewalks outside the establishment. That is city/county responsibility. The muni on rails can be heard on the street from some rooms, which I thought was romantic. It woke me up but it didn't piss me off. And the neighbor garden with all the gnomes! You can only see this from certain rooms, but boy, what a trip! And come on, they have a hot tub. You can walk to the beach and the zoo. I found the proprietors very kind and polite. I recommend it and would stay here again.	
Oct 26 2007 	Wonderful Fun - Especially for Families	My two small children and I stayed at the Ocean Park Motel in August of this year. What a fun experience! We had a two room unit with a kitchen - and while it was small, it was charming and just fine. There were two queen beds, a tiny 1920s bathroom and a tiny 1920's kitchen (w/apt. range and 3/4 size refrigerator) that was perfect. My children loved that I could sit at the end of the tiny table and reach EVERYTHING in the kitchen while sitting down!I am sorry to read that a few people had bad experiences here - the comment about a lack of an elevator had me laughing however. Any homework on this hotel would have told you that! :-) Most of the rooms were on the ground floor - and the buildings are actually on a &quot;campus&quot; of sorts - some surround a courtyard and are in single story buildings - and some branch off on the same property around the on-site parking and garden area and are two-level buildings.Our unit faced the courtyard which was nice and quiet, and we got a nice breeze when we opened up the kitchen window and the front door. There are even covered parking places (first come first get), although they are old fashioned small carports. If you have a big car, it will be a tight squeeze!They do have a little garden area with a &quot;playground&quot; that is really a simple wood play structure with a swing and slide. And it was just fine for two little kids who occasionally wanted to burn off some energy when I just wanted to sit down.The motel is right on the Muni train line (N-Taraval) and a block from the beach and the SF Zoo. There are many fun neighborhood restaurants nearby and a couple of grocery stores within short driving distance (or take the train to 18th and Taraval). There is a killer gelato place (Marco Polo gelato) around 23rd and Taraval (might be off a few blocks) and it has standard and unusual flavors -- all of which are divine!The owners print up a list of recommended restaurants, close-by things to see and do, and services (laundry!). They are kind and nice, and the place is well kept for its age. If you are looking for a place with character in the Sunset, w/easy access to transportation, and a kitchen -- this is a great value for the money.	
Sep 30 2007 	A charming place! Exceeds expectations	Our room on the courtyard was very small but completely sufficient for two nights. Quirky but safe neighborhood filled with endless varieties of rowhouses; great restaurants along Taraval! Our proprietors have really kept the restored motel in great shape, with a peaceful, low-key feeling (you can hear the ocean and the Muni -- all day and night, but it's pleasant). Easy to check in and out. There are no luxuries except peace and quiet and a clean airy place to use as a base camp, especially if you want to retire each night to someplace other than the bustle of downtown SF. We'll return next year!	
